<paragraph pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
The type-specimen (slide no. 202/34) from La Plata (The Argentine) is still present in the Collection. It has some resemblance to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phthiracarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">P. globosus</taxonomicName>
sensu Willmann, but it is larger, the dorsal notogastral hairs are curved to the front, and the anterior anal hair is not curved backwards as in 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phthiracarus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">globosus</taxonomicName>
, but erect.
</paragraph>
